
                                            South Africa, Ireland and France presented their vision and plans to World Rugby Council in London on Monday.

                                         JOHANNESBURG - World Rugby Chairperson Bill Beaumont has hailed the Rugby World Cup 2023 bids as 'exciting and impressive'. South Africa, Ireland and France presented their vision and plans to World Rugby Council in London on Monday. South Africa's bid is promising record profits, the most player-centric tournament ever and a nationwide carnival.Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa led the delegation presenting the bid. The Rugby World Cup company will announce a preferred candidate on 31 October and that recommendation will be put to a vote of the World Rugby Council on 15 November.